---
description: Plan before large changes; inspect existing code first
alwaysApply: true
---

# Planning

- For multi-file, architectural, infra, or reliability-surface changes: produce a short plan before implementing.
- Inspect existing code, docs, and adjacent tests first; extend current patterns instead of inventing parallel ones.
- State objective, constraints, assumptions, acceptance criteria, and out-of-scope items.
- Do not jump into large implementation from a vague prompt — clarify via plan and repo evidence.
- Simple one-file or obvious fixes may skip a formal plan; still read surrounding code.
